lead_paragraph: A drop in Democratic primary turnout has reached deeply into some of the core groups of voters Mrs. Clinton must not only win in November, but also draw in large numbers.

headline.print_headline: Turnout Slips for Democrats in Early Votes
headline.main: Beneath Hillary Clinton’s Super Tuesday Wins, Signs of Turnout Trouble

snippet: A drop in Democratic primary turnout has reached deeply into some of the core groups of voters Mrs. Clinton must not only win in November, but also draw in large numbers.
abstract: Turnout in Democratic primaries so far has been far lower than in 2008, with about three million fewer Democrats participating in 15 caucuses or primaries that have taken place; lack of enthusiasm appear to reach deep into voting blocs Hillary Clinton must win in general election if she is to prevail over Republican nominee, and it stands in stark contrast to record numbers of voters, particularly new voters, who are voting in Republican primaries.
